Expected runtime (ERT in number of f-evaluations) divided by the ERT of the best algorithm from BBOB 2009 in different dimensions. This ERT  ratio and, in braces as dispersion measure, the half difference between 90 and 10%-tile of bootstrapped run lengths appear in the second row of each cell, the best ERT  (preceded by the target ∆f-value in italics) in the first. #succ is the number of trials that reached the target value of the last column. The median number of conducted evaluations is additionally given in italics, if the target in the last column was never reached. Bold entries are statistically significantly better (according to the rank-sum test) compared to the best algorithm from BBOB 2009, with p = 0.05 or p = 10−k when the number k > 1 is following the ↓ symbol, with Bonferroni correction by the number of functions (24).
